title: Ubehage's "Kill My CPU" v1
description:
Ubehage's "Kill My CPU" v1
--------------------------

Here's another small and simple application, with a specific purpose:

This application will start a number of threads, maximizing your CPU-usage to 100%.

When you start this application, you will be asked how many threads you want to start.
If you cancel this dialog, or in some other way fail to write a valid number, the application will cancel and not do anything.

When the threads are being started, there are no windows or icons anywhere to indicate that the CPU is being overloaded.
The processes will run in the background, and can only be terminated using the Windows Task Manager.


/Ubehage
